        "theme":  "Enterprise",
        "summary":  "Generative AI has enabled a new generation of phishing attacks that produce grammatically perfect, contextually accurate messages that defeat traditional rule-based email filters. Amazon Bedrock counters these threats through behavioral analysis and multi-stage pipeline processingΓÇöcombining authentication checks, AI-based contextual analysis, risk scoring, and continuous feedback loopsΓÇöto identify sophisticated impersonation attempts before they reach users.",
        "execSummary":  "The weaponization of generative AI for phishing is collapsing the effectiveness of legacy email security tools, making AI-vs-AI defense architectures an enterprise necessity rather than a future consideration. Bedrock\u0027s behavioral baseline approachΓÇöanalyzing sender patterns and contextual anomalies rather than surface indicatorsΓÇörepresents the correct architectural shift, and the continuous learning feedback loop addresses the adversarial adaptation problem. For customer support and enterprise security leaders, this is directly relevant: AI-generated social engineering targeting support agents and customer-facing systems is an escalating threat vector. Organizations should audit whether their current email and communication security stack has been updated to incorporate LLM-based detection capabilities.",
