        "summary":  "Anthropic\u0027s Claude models are now generally available in Microsoft Foundry on Azure, running on NVIDIA GB300 Blackwell Ultra GPUs with Quantum-X800 InfiniBand networking, enabling enterprises to build and deploy autonomous AI agents for complex business tasks. The release extends the strategic tri-party partnership among Microsoft, NVIDIA, and Anthropic. The offering includes access to NVIDIA agent skills and the Secure Agent Workspace Reference Design for embedding governance and security controls into agent infrastructure.",
        "execSummary":  "Azure-native enterprises now have a fully integrated path to production-grade autonomous agents built on Claude, running on the latest NVIDIA siliconΓÇöremoving the infrastructure friction that has slowed agentic AI adoption. The Secure Agent Workspace Reference Design is particularly significant: it provides a blueprinted approach to embedding AI governance and security controls at the infrastructure layer, not as an afterthought. For customer-support and operations leaders, this means agentic deployments can be stood up with enterprise-grade reliability and compliance baked in from day one. The tri-party alignment of Microsoft, NVIDIA, and Anthropic signals this stack will receive sustained investment and is unlikely to be deprecated near-term.",
