        "date":  "2026-07-03",
        "theme":  "Strategy",
        "summary":  "Workday has implemented a hybrid pricing model combining base subscriptions with Flex Credits for AI agent usage, metering consumption through its Platform Consumption Console. Credit costs vary significantly by taskΓÇöresume screening costs six credits while lead identification requires 750 creditsΓÇöand credits expire annually without rollover. The model introduces budget unpredictability and requires organizations to carefully forecast and govern AI agent spending to avoid overruns.",
        "execSummary":  "Workday\u0027s consumption-based AI pricing is an early signal of a broader industry shift that will fundamentally change how enterprises budget for software. As vendors move from seat licenses to metered agent usage, only 35% of CIOs currently have full visibility into AI operating costsΓÇöa governance gap that will become expensive fast. The variability in credit costs across tasks means finance and IT leaders must build new FinOps competencies specifically for AI agent consumption. Organizations that establish cost monitoring dashboards and ROI frameworks now will be better positioned when this pricing model spreads beyond Workday to other enterprise SaaS vendors.",
