        "theme":  "Strategy",
        "summary":  "CIOs are under mounting board and executive pressure to accelerate AI deployment across their organizations while simultaneously managing unprecedented governance risks. Organizations like Hi Marley and Zuora are structuring teams with built-in tension between innovation and compliance functions to enable faster, safer AI adoption. Key strategies include AI maturity models, risk assessments, and governed platforms that allow controlled experimentation without slowing deployment velocity.",
        "execSummary":  "The central insight here is organizational design, not technology: enterprises that build structured tension between innovation and oversight teams outperform those that treat governance as a gate rather than an enabler. Lengthy approval processes are being replaced by governed experimentation platforms with embedded compliance checks, compressing time-to-value while maintaining risk controls. For senior leaders, this reframes the governance conversation from \u0027how do we slow down risky AI\u0027 to \u0027how do we build infrastructure that makes safe deployment faster.\u0027 The three-part formulaΓÇöorganizational design, graduated maturity frameworks, and problem-first thinkingΓÇöoffers a practical model for enterprise AI transformation leadership.",
