        "execSummary":  "The groupthink problem in LLMs has direct enterprise implications: when AI-powered support, strategy, or analysis tools all converge on the same outputs, they create false consensus at scale rather than surfacing genuine insight. Flint\u0027s approach ΓÇö targeted stochastic injection rather than uniform randomness ΓÇö is technically interesting, but enterprise leaders should focus on the underlying problem it exposes: current frontier models are optimized for average correctness, not epistemic diversity. For teams using LLMs in decision-support, risk analysis, or customer-feedback synthesis, this argues for multi-model strategies or deliberate prompt engineering to stress-test AI conclusions. The startup is early-stage, but the problem it addresses is real and underacknowledged in most enterprise AI deployments.",
